fcMgmtMIB.name: fcMgmtMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of the Fibre Channel Mgmt MIB module.

fcMgmtMIB.contactinfo: Keith McCloghrie Cisco Systems, Inc. Tel: +1 408 526-5260 E-mail: kzm@cisco.com Postal: 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose, CA USA 95134
fcMgmtMIB.description: This module defines management information specific to Fibre Channel-attached devices. Copyright (C) The Internet Society (2005). This version of this MIB module is part of RFC 4044; see the RFC itself for full legal notices.

FcNameIdOrZero.name: FcNameIdOrZero
FcNameIdOrZero.description: The World Wide Name (WWN) associated with a Fibre Channel (FC) entity. WWNs were initially defined as 64-bits in length. The latest definition (for future use) is 128-bits long. The zero-length string value is used in circumstances in which the WWN is unassigned/unknown.

FcAddressIdOrZero.name: FcAddressIdOrZero
FcAddressIdOrZero.description: A Fibre Channel Address ID, a 24-bit value unique within the address space of a Fabric. The zero-length string value is used in circumstances in which the WWN is unassigned/unknown.

FcDomainIdOrZero.name: FcDomainIdOrZero
FcDomainIdOrZero.description: The Domain Id (of an FC switch), or zero if the no Domain Id has been assigned.

FcPortType.name: FcPortType
FcPortType.description: The type of a Fibre Channel port, as indicated by the use of the appropriate value assigned by IANA.
FcPortType.reference: The IANA-maintained registry for Fibre Channel port types (http://www.iana.org/).

FcClasses.name: FcClasses
FcClasses.description: A set of Fibre Channel classes of service.
FcClasses.reference: Classes of service are described in FC-FS Section 13.

FcBbCredit.name: FcBbCredit
FcBbCredit.description: The buffer-to-buffer credit of an FC port.

FcBbCreditModel.name: FcBbCreditModel
FcBbCreditModel.description: The buffer-to-buffer credit model of an Fx_Port.

FcDataFieldSize.name: FcDataFieldSize
FcDataFieldSize.description: The Receive Data Field Size associated with an FC port.

FcUnitFunctions.name: FcUnitFunctions
FcUnitFunctions.description: A set of functions that a Fibre Channel Interconnect Element or Platform might perform. A value with no bits set indicates the function(s) are unknown. The individual bits have the following meanings: other - none of the following. hub - a device that interconnects L_Ports, but does not operate as an FL_Port. switch - a fabric element conforming to the Fibre Channel switch fabric set of standards (e.g., [FC-SW-3]). bridge - a device that encapsulates Fibre Channel frames within another protocol (e.g., [FC-BB], FC-BB-2). gateway - a device that converts an FC-4 to another protocol (e.g., FCP to iSCSI). host - a computer system that provides end users with services such as computation and storage access. storageSubsys - an integrated collection of storage controllers, storage devices, and necessary software that provides storage services to one or more hosts. storageAccessDev - a device that provides storage management and access for heterogeneous hosts and heterogeneous devices (e.g., medium changer). nas - a device that connects to a network and provides file access services. wdmux - a device that modulates/demodulates each of several data streams (e.g., Fibre Channel protocol data streams) onto/from a different part of the light spectrum in an optical fiber. storageDevice - a disk/tape/etc. device (without the controller and/or software required for it to be a 'storageSubsys').

fcmInstanceTable.name: fcmInstanceTable
fcmInstanceTable.description: Information about the local Fibre Channel management instances.

fcmInstanceEntry.name: fcmInstanceEntry
fcmInstanceEntry.description: A list of attributes for a particular local Fibre Channel management instance.

fcmInstanceIndex.name: fcmInstanceIndex
fcmInstanceIndex.description: An arbitrary integer value that uniquely identifies this instance amongst all local Fibre Channel management instances. It is mandatory to keep this value constant between restarts of the agent, and to make every possible effort to keep it constant across restarts (but note, it is unrealistic to expect it to remain constant across all re-configurations of the local system, e.g., across the replacement of all non- volatile storage).

fcmInstanceWwn.name: fcmInstanceWwn
fcmInstanceWwn.description: If the instance has one (or more) WWN(s), then this object contains that (or one of those) WWN(s). If the instance does not have a WWN associated with it, then this object contains the zero-length string.

fcmInstanceFunctions.name: fcmInstanceFunctions
fcmInstanceFunctions.description: One (or more) Fibre Channel unit functions being performed by this instance.

fcmInstancePhysicalIndex.name: fcmInstancePhysicalIndex
fcmInstancePhysicalIndex.reference: entPhysicalIndex is defined in the Entity MIB, RFC 2737.
fcmInstancePhysicalIndex.description: If this management instance corresponds to a physical component (or to a hierarchy of physical components) identified by the Entity-MIB, then this object's value is the value of the entPhysicalIndex of that component (or of the component at the root of that hierarchy). If there is no correspondence to a physical component (or no component that has an entPhysicalIndex value), then the value of this object is zero.

fcmInstanceSoftwareIndex.name: fcmInstanceSoftwareIndex
fcmInstanceSoftwareIndex.reference: hrSWInstalledIndex is defined in the Host Resources MIB, RFC 2790
fcmInstanceSoftwareIndex.description: If this management instance corresponds to an installed software module identified in the Host Resources MIB, then this object's value is the value of the hrSWInstalledIndex of that module. If there is no correspondence to an installed software module (or no module that has a hrSWInstalledIndex value), then the value of this object is zero.

fcmInstanceStatus.name: fcmInstanceStatus
fcmInstanceStatus.description: Overall status of the Fibre Channel entity/entities managed by this management instance. The value should reflect the most serious status of such entities.

fcmInstanceTextName.name: fcmInstanceTextName
fcmInstanceTextName.description: A textual name for this management instance and the Fibre Channel entity/entities that it is managing.

fcmInstanceDescr.name: fcmInstanceDescr
fcmInstanceDescr.description: A textual description of this management instance and the Fibre Channel entity/entities that it is managing.

fcmInstanceFabricId.name: fcmInstanceFabricId
fcmInstanceFabricId.description: The globally unique Fabric Identifier that identifies the fabric to which the Fibre Channel entity/entities managed by this management instance are connected, or, of which they are a part. This is typically the Node WWN of the principal switch of a Fibre Channel fabric. The zero-length string indicates that the fabric identifier is unknown (or not applicable). In the event that the Fibre Channel entity/entities managed by this management instance is/are connected to multiple fabrics, then this object records the first (known) one.

fcmSwitchTable.name: fcmSwitchTable
fcmSwitchTable.description: A table of information about Fibre Channel switches that are managed by Fibre Channel management instances. Each Fibre Channel management instance can manage one or more Fibre Channel switches.

fcmSwitchEntry.name: fcmSwitchEntry
fcmSwitchEntry.description: Information about a particular Fibre Channel switch that is managed by the management instance given by fcmInstanceIndex.

fcmSwitchIndex.name: fcmSwitchIndex
fcmSwitchIndex.description: An arbitrary integer that uniquely identifies a Fibre Channel switch amongst those managed by one Fibre Channel management instance. It is mandatory to keep this value constant between restarts of the agent, and to make every possible effort to keep it constant across restarts.

fcmSwitchDomainId.name: fcmSwitchDomainId
fcmSwitchDomainId.description: The Domain Id of this switch. A value of zero indicates that a switch has not (yet) been assigned a Domain Id.

fcmSwitchPrincipal.name: fcmSwitchPrincipal
fcmSwitchPrincipal.description: An indication of whether this switch is the principal switch within its fabric.

fcmSwitchWWN.name: fcmSwitchWWN
fcmSwitchWWN.description: The World Wide Name of this switch.

fcmPortTable.name: fcmPortTable
fcmPortTable.reference: RFC 2863, The Interfaces Group MIB, June 2000.
fcmPortTable.description: Information about Fibre Channel ports. Each Fibre Channel port is represented by one entry in the IF-MIB's ifTable.

fcmPortEntry.name: fcmPortEntry
fcmPortEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a specific port.

fcmPortInstanceIndex.name: fcmPortInstanceIndex
fcmPortInstanceIndex.description: The value of fcmInstanceIndex by which the Fibre Channel management instance, which manages this port, is identified in the fcmInstanceTable.

fcmPortWwn.name: fcmPortWwn
fcmPortWwn.description: The World Wide Name of the port, or the zero-length string if the port does not have a WWN.

fcmPortNodeWwn.name: fcmPortNodeWwn
fcmPortNodeWwn.description: The World Wide Name of the Node that contains this port, or the zero-length string if the port does not have a node WWN.

fcmPortAdminType.name: fcmPortAdminType
fcmPortAdminType.description: The administratively desired type of this port.

fcmPortOperType.name: fcmPortOperType
fcmPortOperType.description: The current operational type of this port.

fcmPortFcCapClass.name: fcmPortFcCapClass
fcmPortFcCapClass.description: The classes of service capability of this port.

fcmPortFcOperClass.name: fcmPortFcOperClass
fcmPortFcOperClass.description: The classes of service that are currently operational on this port. For an FL_Port, this is the union of the classes being supported across all attached NL_Ports.

fcmPortTransmitterType.name: fcmPortTransmitterType
fcmPortTransmitterType.description: The technology of the port transceiver.

fcmPortConnectorType.name: fcmPortConnectorType
fcmPortConnectorType.description: The module type of the port connector. This object refers to the hardware implementation of the port. It will be 'embedded' if the hardware equivalent to Gigabit interface card (GBIC) is part of the line card and is unremovable. It will be 'glm' if it's a gigabit link module (GLM). It will be 'gbicSerialId' if the GBIC serial id can be read, else it will be 'gbicNoSerialId'. It will be 'sfpSerialId' if the small form factor (SFP) pluggable GBICs serial id can be read, else it will be 'sfpNoSerialId'.

fcmPortSerialNumber.name: fcmPortSerialNumber
fcmPortSerialNumber.description: The serial number associated with the port (e.g., for a GBIC). If not applicable, the object's value is a zero- length string.

fcmPortPhysicalNumber.name: fcmPortPhysicalNumber
fcmPortPhysicalNumber.description: This is the port's 'Physical Port Number' as defined by GS-3.

fcmPortAdminSpeed.name: fcmPortAdminSpeed
fcmPortAdminSpeed.description: The speed of the interface: 'auto' - auto-negotiation 'tenGbs' - 10Gbs 'fourGbs' - 4Gbs 'twoGbs' - 2Gbs 'oneGbs' - 1Gbs 'halfGbs' - 500Mbs 'quarterGbs' - 250Mbs 'eighthGbs' - 125Mbs

fcmPortCapProtocols.name: fcmPortCapProtocols
fcmPortCapProtocols.description: A bit mask specifying the higher level protocols that are capable of running over this port. Note that for generic Fx_Ports, E_Ports, and B_Ports, this object will indicate all protocols.

fcmPortOperProtocols.name: fcmPortOperProtocols
fcmPortOperProtocols.description: A bit mask specifying the higher level protocols that are currently operational on this port. For Fx_Ports, E_Ports, and B_Ports, this object will typically have the value 'unknown'.

fcmPortStatsTable.name: fcmPortStatsTable
fcmPortStatsTable.description: A list of statistics for Fibre Channel ports.

fcmPortStatsEntry.name: fcmPortStatsEntry
fcmPortStatsEntry.reference: The Interfaces Group MIB, RFC 2863, June 2000.
fcmPortStatsEntry.description: An entry containing statistics for a Fibre Channel port. If any counter in this table suffers a discontinuity, the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime (defined in the IF-MIB) must be updated.

fcmPortBBCreditZeros.name: fcmPortBBCreditZeros
fcmPortBBCreditZeros.description: The number of transitions in/out of the buffer-to-buffer credit zero state. The other side is not providing any credit.

fcmPortFullInputBuffers.name: fcmPortFullInputBuffers
fcmPortFullInputBuffers.description: The number of occurrences when all input buffers of a port were full and outbound buffer-to-buffer credit transitioned to zero, i.e., there became no credit to provide to other side.

fcmPortClass2RxFrames.name: fcmPortClass2RxFrames
fcmPortClass2RxFrames.description: The number of Class 2 frames received at this port.

fcmPortClass2RxOctets.name: fcmPortClass2RxOctets
fcmPortClass2RxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 2 frames received at this port.

fcmPortClass2TxFrames.name: fcmPortClass2TxFrames
fcmPortClass2TxFrames.description: The number of Class 2 frames transmitted out of this port.

fcmPortClass2TxOctets.name: fcmPortClass2TxOctets
fcmPortClass2TxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 2 frames transmitted out of this port.

fcmPortClass2Discards.name: fcmPortClass2Discards
fcmPortClass2Discards.description: The number of Class 2 frames that were discarded upon reception at this port.

fcmPortClass2RxFbsyFrames.name: fcmPortClass2RxFbsyFrames
fcmPortClass2RxFbsyFrames.description: The number of times that F_BSY was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered to the other end of the link. This can occur when either the fabric or the destination port is temporarily busy. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

fcmPortClass2RxPbsyFrames.name: fcmPortClass2RxPbsyFrames
fcmPortClass2RxPbsyFrames.description: The number of times that P_BSY was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered to the other end of the link. This can occur when the destination port is temporarily busy.

fcmPortClass2RxFrjtFrames.name: fcmPortClass2RxFrjtFrames
fcmPortClass2RxFrjtFrames.description: The number of times that F_RJT was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that was rejected by the fabric. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

fcmPortClass2RxPrjtFrames.name: fcmPortClass2RxPrjtFrames
fcmPortClass2RxPrjtFrames.description: The number of times that P_RJT was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that was rejected at the destination N_Port.

fcmPortClass2TxFbsyFrames.name: fcmPortClass2TxFbsyFrames
fcmPortClass2TxFbsyFrames.description: The number of times that F_BSY was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered because either the Fabric or the destination port was temporarily busy. Note that this counter will never increment for an N_Port.

fcmPortClass2TxPbsyFrames.name: fcmPortClass2TxPbsyFrames
fcmPortClass2TxPbsyFrames.description: The number of times that P_BSY was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered because the destination port was temporarily busy. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

fcmPortClass2TxFrjtFrames.name: fcmPortClass2TxFrjtFrames
fcmPortClass2TxFrjtFrames.description: The number of times that F_RJT was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame being rejected by the fabric. Note that this counter will never increment for an N_Port.

fcmPortClass2TxPrjtFrames.name: fcmPortClass2TxPrjtFrames
fcmPortClass2TxPrjtFrames.description: The number of times that P_RJT was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame being rejected at the destination N_Port. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

fcmPortClass3RxFrames.name: fcmPortClass3RxFrames
fcmPortClass3RxFrames.description: The number of Class 3 frames received at this port.

fcmPortClass3RxOctets.name: fcmPortClass3RxOctets
fcmPortClass3RxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 3 frames received at this port.

fcmPortClass3TxFrames.name: fcmPortClass3TxFrames
fcmPortClass3TxFrames.description: The number of Class 3 frames transmitted out of this port.

fcmPortClass3TxOctets.name: fcmPortClass3TxOctets
fcmPortClass3TxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 3 frames transmitted out of this port.

fcmPortClass3Discards.name: fcmPortClass3Discards
fcmPortClass3Discards.description: The number of Class 3 frames that were discarded upon reception at this port.

fcmPortClassFRxFrames.name: fcmPortClassFRxFrames
fcmPortClassFRxFrames.description: The number of Class F frames received at this port.

fcmPortClassFRxOctets.name: fcmPortClassFRxOctets
fcmPortClassFRxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class F frames received at this port.

fcmPortClassFTxFrames.name: fcmPortClassFTxFrames
fcmPortClassFTxFrames.description: The number of Class F frames transmitted out of this port.

fcmPortClassFTxOctets.name: fcmPortClassFTxOctets
fcmPortClassFTxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class F frames transmitted out of this port.

fcmPortClassFDiscards.name: fcmPortClassFDiscards
fcmPortClassFDiscards.description: The number of Class F frames that were discarded upon reception at this port.

fcmPortLcStatsTable.name: fcmPortLcStatsTable
fcmPortLcStatsTable.description: A list of Counter32-based statistics for systems that do not support Counter64.

fcmPortLcStatsEntry.name: fcmPortLcStatsEntry
fcmPortLcStatsEntry.reference: The Interfaces Group MIB, RFC 2863, June 2000.
fcmPortLcStatsEntry.description: An entry containing low-capacity (i.e., based on Counter32) statistics for a Fibre Channel port. If any counter in this table suffers a discontinuity, the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime (defined in the IF-MIB) must be updated.

fcmPortLcBBCreditZeros.name: fcmPortLcBBCreditZeros
fcmPortLcBBCreditZeros.description: The number of transitions in/out of the buffer-to-buffer credit zero state. The other side is not providing any credit.

fcmPortLcFullInputBuffers.name: fcmPortLcFullInputBuffers
fcmPortLcFullInputBuffers.description: The number of occurrences when all input buffers of a port were full and outbound buffer-to-buffer credit transitioned to zero, i.e., there became no credit to provide to other side.

fcmPortLcClass2RxFrames.name: fcmPortLcClass2RxFrames
fcmPortLcClass2RxFrames.description: The number of Class 2 frames received at this port.

fcmPortLcClass2RxOctets.name: fcmPortLcClass2RxOctets
fcmPortLcClass2RxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 2 frames received at this port.

fcmPortLcClass2TxFrames.name: fcmPortLcClass2TxFrames
fcmPortLcClass2TxFrames.description: The number of Class 2 frames transmitted out of this port.

fcmPortLcClass2TxOctets.name: fcmPortLcClass2TxOctets
fcmPortLcClass2TxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 2 frames transmitted out of this port.

fcmPortLcClass2Discards.name: fcmPortLcClass2Discards
fcmPortLcClass2Discards.description: The number of Class 2 frames that were discarded upon reception at this port.

fcmPortLcClass2RxFbsyFrames.name: fcmPortLcClass2RxFbsyFrames
fcmPortLcClass2RxFbsyFrames.description: The number of times that F_BSY was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered to the other end of the link. This can occur when either the fabric or the destination port is temporarily busy. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

fcmPortLcClass2RxPbsyFrames.name: fcmPortLcClass2RxPbsyFrames
fcmPortLcClass2RxPbsyFrames.description: The number of times that P_BSY was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered to the other end of the link. This can occur when the destination port is temporarily busy.

fcmPortLcClass2RxFrjtFrames.name: fcmPortLcClass2RxFrjtFrames
fcmPortLcClass2RxFrjtFrames.description: The number of times that F_RJT was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that was rejected by the fabric. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

fcmPortLcClass2RxPrjtFrames.name: fcmPortLcClass2RxPrjtFrames
fcmPortLcClass2RxPrjtFrames.description: The number of times that P_RJT was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that was rejected at the destination N_Port.

fcmPortLcClass2TxFbsyFrames.name: fcmPortLcClass2TxFbsyFrames
fcmPortLcClass2TxFbsyFrames.description: The number of times that F_BSY was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered because either the Fabric or the destination port was temporarily busy. Note that this counter will never increment for an N_Port.

fcmPortLcClass2TxPbsyFrames.name: fcmPortLcClass2TxPbsyFrames
fcmPortLcClass2TxPbsyFrames.description: The number of times that P_BSY was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered because the destination port was temporarily busy. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

fcmPortLcClass2TxFrjtFrames.name: fcmPortLcClass2TxFrjtFrames
fcmPortLcClass2TxFrjtFrames.description: The number of times that F_RJT was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame being rejected by the fabric. Note that this counter will never increment for an N_Port.

fcmPortLcClass2TxPrjtFrames.name: fcmPortLcClass2TxPrjtFrames
fcmPortLcClass2TxPrjtFrames.description: The number of times that P_RJT was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame being rejected at the destination N_Port. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

fcmPortLcClass3RxFrames.name: fcmPortLcClass3RxFrames
fcmPortLcClass3RxFrames.description: The number of Class 3 frames received at this port.

fcmPortLcClass3RxOctets.name: fcmPortLcClass3RxOctets
fcmPortLcClass3RxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 3 frames received at this port.

fcmPortLcClass3TxFrames.name: fcmPortLcClass3TxFrames
fcmPortLcClass3TxFrames.description: The number of Class 3 frames transmitted out of this port.

fcmPortLcClass3TxOctets.name: fcmPortLcClass3TxOctets
fcmPortLcClass3TxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 3 frames transmitted out of this port.

fcmPortLcClass3Discards.name: fcmPortLcClass3Discards
fcmPortLcClass3Discards.description: The number of Class 3 frames that were discarded upon reception at this port.

fcmPortErrorsTable.name: fcmPortErrorsTable
fcmPortErrorsTable.description: Error counters for Fibre Channel ports.

fcmPortErrorsEntry.name: fcmPortErrorsEntry
fcmPortErrorsEntry.reference: The Interfaces Group MIB, RFC 2863, June 2000.
fcmPortErrorsEntry.description: Error counters for a Fibre Channel port. If any counter in this table suffers a discontinuity, the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime (defined in the IF-MIB) must be updated.

fcmPortRxLinkResets.name: fcmPortRxLinkResets
fcmPortRxLinkResets.description: The number of Link Reset (LR) Primitive Sequences received.

fcmPortTxLinkResets.name: fcmPortTxLinkResets
fcmPortTxLinkResets.description: The number of Link Reset (LR) Primitive Sequences transmitted.

fcmPortLinkResets.name: fcmPortLinkResets
fcmPortLinkResets.description: The number of times the reset link protocol was initiated on this port. This includes the number of Loop Initialization Primitive (LIP) events on an arbitrated loop port.

fcmPortRxOfflineSequences.name: fcmPortRxOfflineSequences
fcmPortRxOfflineSequences.description: The number of Offline (OLS) Primitive Sequences received at this port.

fcmPortTxOfflineSequences.name: fcmPortTxOfflineSequences
fcmPortTxOfflineSequences.description: The number of Offline (OLS) Primitive Sequences transmitted by this port.

fcmPortLinkFailures.name: fcmPortLinkFailures
fcmPortLinkFailures.description: The number of link failures. This count is part of FC-PH's Link Error Status Block (LESB).

fcmPortLossofSynchs.name: fcmPortLossofSynchs
fcmPortLossofSynchs.description: The number of instances of synchronization loss detected at this port. This count is part of FC-PH's Link Error Status Block (LESB).

fcmPortLossofSignals.name: fcmPortLossofSignals
fcmPortLossofSignals.description: The number of instances of signal loss detected at this port. This count is part of FC-PH's Link Error Status Block (LESB).

fcmPortPrimSeqProtocolErrors.name: fcmPortPrimSeqProtocolErrors
fcmPortPrimSeqProtocolErrors.description: The number of primitive sequence protocol errors detected at this port. This count is part of FC-PH's Link Error Status Block (LESB).

fcmPortInvalidTxWords.name: fcmPortInvalidTxWords
fcmPortInvalidTxWords.description: The number of invalid transmission words received at this port. This count is part of FC-PH's Link Error Status Block (LESB).

fcmPortInvalidCRCs.name: fcmPortInvalidCRCs
fcmPortInvalidCRCs.description: The number of frames received with an invalid CRC. This count is part of FC-PH's Link Error Status Block (LESB).

fcmPortInvalidOrderedSets.name: fcmPortInvalidOrderedSets
fcmPortInvalidOrderedSets.description: The number of invalid ordered sets received at this port.

fcmPortFrameTooLongs.name: fcmPortFrameTooLongs
fcmPortFrameTooLongs.description: The number of frames received at this port for which the frame length was greater than what was agreed to in FLOGI/PLOGI. This could be caused by losing the end of frame delimiter.

fcmPortTruncatedFrames.name: fcmPortTruncatedFrames
fcmPortTruncatedFrames.description: The number of frames received at this port for which the frame length was less than the minimum indicated by the frame header - normally 24 bytes, but it could be more if the DFCTL field indicates an optional header should have been present.

fcmPortAddressErrors.name: fcmPortAddressErrors
fcmPortAddressErrors.description: The number of frames received with unknown addressing; for example, an unknown SID or DID.

fcmPortDelimiterErrors.name: fcmPortDelimiterErrors
fcmPortDelimiterErrors.description: The number of invalid frame delimiters received at this port. An example is a frame with a class 2 start and a class 3 at the end.

fcmPortEncodingDisparityErrors.name: fcmPortEncodingDisparityErrors
fcmPortEncodingDisparityErrors.description: The number of encoding disparity errors received at this port.

fcmPortOtherErrors.name: fcmPortOtherErrors
fcmPortOtherErrors.description: The number of errors that were detected on this port but not counted by any other error counter in this row.

fcmFxPortTable.name: fcmFxPortTable
fcmFxPortTable.description: Additional information about Fibre Channel ports that is specific to Fx_Ports. This table will contain one entry for each fcmPortTable entry that represents an Fx_Port.

fcmFxPortEntry.name: fcmFxPortEntry
fcmFxPortEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a specific Fx_Port.

fcmFxPortRatov.name: fcmFxPortRatov
fcmFxPortRatov.description: The Resource_Allocation_Timeout Value configured for this Fx_Port. This is used as the timeout value for determining when to reuse an Nx_Port resource such as a Recovery_Qualifier. It represents the Error_Detect_Timeout value (see fcmFxPortEdtov) plus twice the maximum time that a frame may be delayed within the Fabric and still be delivered.

fcmFxPortEdtov.name: fcmFxPortEdtov
fcmFxPortEdtov.description: The Error_Detect_Timeout value configured for this Fx_Port. This is used as the timeout value for detecting an error condition.

fcmFxPortRttov.name: fcmFxPortRttov
fcmFxPortRttov.description: The Receiver_Transmitter_Timeout value of this Fx_Port. This is used by the receiver logic to detect a Loss of Synchronization.

fcmFxPortHoldTime.name: fcmFxPortHoldTime
fcmFxPortHoldTime.description: The maximum time that this Fx_Port shall hold a frame before discarding the frame if it is unable to deliver the frame. The value 0 means that this Fx_Port does not support this parameter.

fcmFxPortCapBbCreditMax.name: fcmFxPortCapBbCreditMax
fcmFxPortCapBbCreditMax.description: The maximum number of receive buffers that this port is capable of making available for holding frames from attached Nx_Port(s).

fcmFxPortCapBbCreditMin.name: fcmFxPortCapBbCreditMin
fcmFxPortCapBbCreditMin.description: The minimum number of receive buffers that this port is capable of making available for holding frames from attached Nx_Port(s).

fcmFxPortCapDataFieldSizeMax.name: fcmFxPortCapDataFieldSizeMax
fcmFxPortCapDataFieldSizeMax.description: The maximum size in bytes of the Data Field in a frame that this Fx_Port is capable of receiving from an attached Nx_Port.

fcmFxPortCapDataFieldSizeMin.name: fcmFxPortCapDataFieldSizeMin
fcmFxPortCapDataFieldSizeMin.description: The minimum size in bytes of the Data Field in a frame that this Fx_Port is capable of receiving from an attached Nx_Port.

fcmFxPortCapClass2SeqDeliv.name: fcmFxPortCapClass2SeqDeliv
fcmFxPortCapClass2SeqDeliv.description: An indication of whether this Fx_Port is capable of supporting Class 2 Sequential Delivery.

fcmFxPortCapClass3SeqDeliv.name: fcmFxPortCapClass3SeqDeliv
fcmFxPortCapClass3SeqDeliv.description: An indication of whether this Fx_Port is capable of supporting Class 3 Sequential Delivery.

fcmFxPortCapHoldTimeMax.name: fcmFxPortCapHoldTimeMax
fcmFxPortCapHoldTimeMax.description: The maximum holding time that this Fx_Port is capable of supporting.

fcmFxPortCapHoldTimeMin.name: fcmFxPortCapHoldTimeMin
fcmFxPortCapHoldTimeMin.description: The minimum holding time that this Fx_Port is capable of supporting.

fcmISPortTable.name: fcmISPortTable
fcmISPortTable.description: Additional information about E_Ports, B_Ports, and any other type of Fibre Channel port to which inter-switch links can be connected. This table will contain one entry for each fcmPortTable entry that represents such a port.

fcmISPortEntry.name: fcmISPortEntry
fcmISPortEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a specific port connected to an inter-switch link.

fcmISPortClassFCredit.name: fcmISPortClassFCredit
fcmISPortClassFCredit.description: The maximum number of Class F data frames that can be transmitted by the inter-switch port without receipt of ACK or Link_Response frames.

fcmISPortClassFDataFieldSize.name: fcmISPortClassFDataFieldSize
fcmISPortClassFDataFieldSize.description: The Receive Data Field Size that the inter-switch port has agreed to support for Class F frames to/from this port. The size specifies the largest Data Field Size for an FT_1 frame.

fcmFLoginTable.name: fcmFLoginTable
fcmFLoginTable.description: A table that contains one entry for each Nx_Port logged- in/attached to a particular Fx_Port in the switch. Each entry contains the services parameters established during the most recent Fabric Login, explicit or implicit. Note that an Fx_Port may have one or more Nx_Ports attached to it.

fcmFLoginEntry.name: fcmFLoginEntry
fcmFLoginEntry.description: An entry containing service parameters established from a successful Fabric Login.

fcmFLoginNxPortIndex.name: fcmFLoginNxPortIndex
fcmFLoginNxPortIndex.reference: The Interfaces Group MIB, RFC 2863, June 2000.
fcmFLoginNxPortIndex.description: An arbitrary integer that uniquely identifies an Nx_Port amongst all those attached to the Fx_Port indicated by ifIndex. After a value of this object is assigned to a particular Nx_Port, that value can be re-used when and only when it is assigned to the same Nx_Port, or, after a reset of the value of the relevant instance of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

fcmFLoginPortWwn.name: fcmFLoginPortWwn
fcmFLoginPortWwn.description: The port name of the attached Nx_Port, or the zero-length string if unknown.

fcmFLoginNodeWwn.name: fcmFLoginNodeWwn
fcmFLoginNodeWwn.description: The node name of the attached Nx_Port, or the zero-length string if unknown.

fcmFLoginBbCreditModel.name: fcmFLoginBbCreditModel
fcmFLoginBbCreditModel.description: The buffer-to-buffer credit model in use by the Fx_Port.

fcmFLoginBbCredit.name: fcmFLoginBbCredit
fcmFLoginBbCredit.description: The number of buffers available for holding frames to be transmitted to the attached Nx_Port. These buffers are for buffer-to-buffer flow control in the direction from Fx_Port to Nx_Port.

fcmFLoginClassesAgreed.name: fcmFLoginClassesAgreed
fcmFLoginClassesAgreed.description: The Classes of Service that the Fx_Port has agreed to support for this Nx_Port.

fcmFLoginClass2SeqDelivAgreed.name: fcmFLoginClass2SeqDelivAgreed
fcmFLoginClass2SeqDelivAgreed.description: An indication of whether the Fx_Port has agreed to support Class 2 sequential delivery for this Nx_Port. This is only meaningful if Class 2 service has been agreed upon.

fcmFLoginClass2DataFieldSize.name: fcmFLoginClass2DataFieldSize
fcmFLoginClass2DataFieldSize.description: The Receive Data Field Size that the Fx_Port has agreed to support for Class 2 frames to/from this Nx_Port. The size specifies the largest Data Field Size for an FT_1 frame. This is only meaningful if Class 2 service has been agreed upon.

fcmFLoginClass3SeqDelivAgreed.name: fcmFLoginClass3SeqDelivAgreed
fcmFLoginClass3SeqDelivAgreed.description: An indication of whether the Fx_Port has agreed to support Class 3 sequential delivery for this Nx_Port. This is only meaningful if Class 3 service has been agreed upon.

fcmFLoginClass3DataFieldSize.name: fcmFLoginClass3DataFieldSize
fcmFLoginClass3DataFieldSize.description: The Receive Data Field Size that the Fx_Port has agreed to support for Class 3 frames to/from this Nx_Port. The size specifies the largest Data Field Size for an FT_1 frame. This is only meaningful if Class 3 service has been agreed upon.

fcmLinkTable.name: fcmLinkTable
fcmLinkTable.description: A table containing any Fibre Channel link information that is known to local Fibre Channel managed instances. One end of such a link is typically at a local port, but the table can also contain information on links for which neither end is a local port. If one end of a link terminates locally, then that end is termed 'end1'; the other end is termed 'end2'.

fcmLinkEntry.name: fcmLinkEntry
fcmLinkEntry.description: An entry containing information that a particular Fibre Channel managed instance has about a Fibre Channel link. The two ends of the link are called 'end1' and 'end2'.

fcmLinkIndex.name: fcmLinkIndex
fcmLinkIndex.description: An arbitrary integer that uniquely identifies one link within the set of links about which a particular managed instance has information.

fcmLinkEnd1NodeWwn.name: fcmLinkEnd1NodeWwn
fcmLinkEnd1NodeWwn.description: The node name of end1, or the zero-length string if unknown.

fcmLinkEnd1PhysPortNumber.name: fcmLinkEnd1PhysPortNumber
fcmLinkEnd1PhysPortNumber.description: The physical port number of end1, or zero if unknown.

fcmLinkEnd1PortWwn.name: fcmLinkEnd1PortWwn
fcmLinkEnd1PortWwn.description: The port WWN of end1, or the zero-length string if unknown. ('end1' is local if this value is equal to the value of fcmPortWwn in one of the rows of the fcmPortTable.)

fcmLinkEnd2NodeWwn.name: fcmLinkEnd2NodeWwn
fcmLinkEnd2NodeWwn.description: The node name of end2, or the zero-length string if unknown.

fcmLinkEnd2PhysPortNumber.name: fcmLinkEnd2PhysPortNumber
fcmLinkEnd2PhysPortNumber.description: The physical port number of end2, or zero if unknown.

fcmLinkEnd2PortWwn.name: fcmLinkEnd2PortWwn
fcmLinkEnd2PortWwn.description: The port WWN of end2, or the zero-length string if unknown.

fcmLinkEnd2AgentAddress.name: fcmLinkEnd2AgentAddress
fcmLinkEnd2AgentAddress.description: The address of the management agent for the Fibre Channel Interconnect Element or Platform of which end2 is a part. The GS-4 specification provides some information about management agents. If the address is unknown, the value of this object is the zero-length string.

fcmLinkEnd2UnitType.name: fcmLinkEnd2UnitType
fcmLinkEnd2UnitType.description: The type of/function(s) performed by the Fibre Channel Interconnect Element or Platform of which end2 is a part.

fcmLinkEnd2FcAddressId.name: fcmLinkEnd2FcAddressId
fcmLinkEnd2FcAddressId.description: The Fibre Channel Address ID of end2, or the zero-length string if unknown.

fcmgmtCompliance.name: fcmgmtCompliance
fcmgmtCompliance.description: Describes the requirements for compliance to this Fibre Channel Management MIB.

fcmInstanceBasicGroup.name: fcmInstanceBasicGroup
fcmInstanceBasicGroup.description: Basic information about Fibre Channel managed instances.

fcmSwitchBasicGroup.name: fcmSwitchBasicGroup
fcmSwitchBasicGroup.description: Basic information about Fibre Channel switches.

fcmPortBasicGroup.name: fcmPortBasicGroup
fcmPortBasicGroup.description: Basic information about Fibre Channel ports.

fcmPortStatsGroup.name: fcmPortStatsGroup
fcmPortStatsGroup.description: Traffic statistics, which are not specific to any one class of service, for Fibre Channel ports.

fcmPortClass23StatsGroup.name: fcmPortClass23StatsGroup
fcmPortClass23StatsGroup.description: Traffic statistics for Class 2 and Class 3 traffic on Fibre Channel ports.

fcmPortClassFStatsGroup.name: fcmPortClassFStatsGroup
fcmPortClassFStatsGroup.description: Traffic statistics for Class F traffic on Fibre Channel ports.

fcmPortLcStatsGroup.name: fcmPortLcStatsGroup
fcmPortLcStatsGroup.description: Low-capacity (32-bit) statistics for Fibre Channel ports.

fcmPortErrorsGroup.name: fcmPortErrorsGroup
fcmPortErrorsGroup.description: Error statistics for Fibre Channel ports.

fcmSwitchPortGroup.name: fcmSwitchPortGroup
fcmSwitchPortGroup.description: Information about ports on a Fibre Channel switch.

fcmSwitchLoginGroup.name: fcmSwitchLoginGroup
fcmSwitchLoginGroup.description: Information known to a Fibre Channel switch about attached/logged-in Nx_Ports.
